            <div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2023_01">
                
                <p n="1">
                    Fortune! Prosperity!
                </p>
                <p n="1">
                    This is the 12th year of Kōpparakesarivarman.
                </p>
                <p n="1-4">
                    For Mahādeva of Śrī Vijaiyamaṅgalam of big Śrī Vāṉavan-mahādevi-catturvedimaṅgalam, a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> on the northern bank, Ampalavaṉ Paḻuvūr Nakkaṉ alias Śrī Vikramacōḻa Mārāyaṉ, who made <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ceyvitta</foreign></supplied> this holy stone temple <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ittirukkaṟṟaḷi</foreign></supplied>, gave <supplied reason="subaudible">for</supplied> 4, four, perpetual lamps, as long as the sun and the moon endure.
                </p>
                <p n="4-5">
                    At the rate of ninety-six goats for one <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> of <foreign>ghee</foreign> every day for one lamp, three hundred and eighty-four goats for one <foreign>nāḻi</foreign> of <foreign>ghee</foreign> every day for four lamps, as long as the sun and the moon endure, <supplied reason="subaudible">he</supplied> gave <supplied reason="subaudible">those 384</supplied> non dying non ageing great goats.
                </p>
                <p n="5-6">
                    Those are under the protection of the Panmāheśvaras.</p>
            </div>
            
